The paper deals with the study of rank logic, an extension of fixed-point logic with counting, and its expressive power in relation to polynomial time. This topic falls under the area of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of matrices and linear equation systems, which are common topics in computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG).
